CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper October 22, 1955, pg. 7, reads: "Centre - Roberts Staff -  The Centre-Roberts Garage, 72 Roberts Street, manned by factory-trained mechanics, is one of the finest and most modern garages in Pittsburgh.  The new establishment will hold its grand opening Saturday, Oct. 22.  Left to right, part of the factory-trained staff: Willie Cummings, F. Paye, Camuel (Spuddy) Spearman and Joe Talley - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Willie Cummings, F. Paye, Camuel "Spuddy" Spearman, and Joe Talley standing in Centre - Roberts Garage with signs reading "Lubrication Beat....!" and "Change Motor Oil," 72 Roberts Street,
